  "body": "### Context\r\nAs a user, I need sensible defaults for Mainnet that reflect the reality of the client in 2023. Today, Forest and Fast sync are default. These are great for private networks, but a bad UX on Mainnet. This issue explores the change of defaults for 23.10.0 release.\r\n\r\n### To-Do\r\n- [ ] Full flat DB\r\n- [ ] Data storage format --> Bonsai\r\n    - [ ] Evaluate for Private networks (wait on Bonsai Archive work?)  \r\n- [ ] Sync mode --> Snap? (do we want to wait for snap sync server)\r\n    - [ ] Evaluate for private networks? (cant serve data on snap)\r\n- [ ] Evaluate split defaults for private vs public networks",
